article.headline: Oregon 79, Oregon St. 66
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. -- Damyean Dotson scored 21 points and Oregon used a 9-0 second-half run to hold off rival Oregon State 79-66 Sunday night in the Pac-12 Conference opener for both teams. E.J. Singler added 15 points and nine rebounds for the Ducks (12-2). Ahmad Starks had 22 points, and Roberto Nelson 18 for Oregon State (10-4). Dotson, a freshman guard, scored seven points in Oregon's 15-2 run to open the second half, helping the Ducks turn the tide and take a 43-36 lead. Oregon State came right back, with Devon Collier scoring seven consecutive points to tie the game. The Beavers took a 47-46 lead on Starks' two free throws with 11:02 remaining. But Oregon took the momentum for good, scoring nine straight points over 3 1/2 minutes. Arsalan Kazemi's basket off an offensive rebound gave the Ducks a 55-47 lead with 7:34 remaining. Oregon State got no closer than five after that.
